      <title>Re: cjw_newsletter vs eznewsletter</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/cjw_newsletter/forum/feature_requests/cjw_newsletter_vs_eznewsletter/re_cjw_newsletter_vs_eznewsletter</link>
      <description>Hi,&#13;
&#13;
here are some post on share.ez.no&#13;
&#13;
http://share.ez.no/forums/setup-design/ez-newsletter-vs-cjw-newsletter/%28language%29/eng-GB&#13;
&#13;
The current doc is placed in the actual extension doc folder, here is the link directly from github&#13;
&#13;
https://github.com/cjw-network/cjw_newsletter/blob/stable-1.0/doc/cjw_newsletter_documentation.pdf?raw=true&#13;
&#13;
The main goal of CJW Newsletter was to have a newsletter which is easy to install on existing ez publish installations. The whole newsletter list and editions configuration is done with normal contentobjects with special datatypes. &#13;
We have only 1 ini cjw_newsletter.ini and 1 extension.&#13;
&#13;
Regards&#13;
FElix&#13;
&#13;
</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Felix Woldt)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/cjw_newsletter/forum/feature_requests/cjw_newsletter_vs_eznewsletter/re_cjw_newsletter_vs_eznewsletter</guid>
